# Shell scripts run inside Linux containers via their shebang line - a CRLF
# line ending corrupts `#!/bin/sh` into an unresolvable interpreter path
# (`/bin/sh\r`), which fails with a confusing "no such file or directory".
# Force LF regardless of core.autocrlf so this can't reappear on a Windows
# checkout (this exact bug happened once already: the entrypoint script came
# back as CRLF after a branch merge and crash-looped the orchestrator).
*.sh text eol=lf
